  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Fluconazole is the first-line agent in the treatment of invasive candidiasis. Studies showed
      inappropriate drug exposure causes high mortality in critically ill patients. Under-dosing
      and ineffective fluconazole trough serum concentrations were found in a recent retrospective
      study. Variability in fluconazole exposure can be easily measured with therapeutic drug
      monitoring. For patient groups who are at risk for drug underexposure, therapeutic drug
      monitoring can be valuable regards decreasing mortality.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
